 Appendix B: Links to code repositories used in the research.
 Appendix C: Proposal for a platform supporting independent researchers.
 Appendix D: Resources curated for individuals conducting independent research.
Part 9: The Community Platform
NIRA (Neophyte Independent Research Alliance)
The Neophyte Independent Research Alliance (NIRA) is designed to support and foster
independent research through a collaborative, accessible, and rigorous platform. Below is
an overview of its structure, processes, resources, mentorship opportunities, recognition
mechanisms, and community rules.
1. Online Forum/Platform
NIRA operates primarily through an online community, with a Discord server as a free and
user-friendly entry point. A dedicated website will host links to the Discord and provide
additional features. The platform is organized by discipline, ensuring focused discussion
and collaboration within specific fields. Updates will be posted on GitHub when the site
and Discord are live.
2. Channels/Sections
The community is divided into clearly defined channels for main domains, each featuring
dedicated subdomains for deeper engagement. For example:
 Mathematics
 Number Theory
 Probability Theory
 Advanced Algebra
 Geometry
 Other Specializations
Physics
Classical Mechanics
Quantum Physics
Thermodynamics
Astrophysics
Other Specializations
Biology
Molecular Biology
Ecology
Genetics
Evolutionary Biology
Other Specializations
Chemistry
Organic Chemistry
Inorganic Chemistry
Physical Chemistry
Biochemistry
Other Specializations
Engineering
Electrical Engineering
Mechanical Engineering
Civil Engineering
Computer Engineering
Other Specializations
Cross-domain
Methodology
Resources
Success stories
These sections and their subdomains enable members to engage with precisely targeted
content, fostering both specialization and interdisciplinary collaboration.
3. Verification Process
To maintain high standards, NIRA uses a multi-step verification process for submitted
research:
 Members post their work within the relevant channels and subdomains.
 Other community members review and provide feedback.
 AI-assisted verification augments human review.
 Collaborative refinement ensures improvements and accuracy.
 Community endorsement highlights validated contributions.
4. Resources
NIRA provides a comprehensive suite of resources to facilitate research and publication,
including:
 AI prompt templates for eƯective communication and analysis
 Verification checklists to guide rigorous evaluation
 Methodology guides for best practices in research
 Publication pathways to help share findings with a wider audience
 Funding sources for independent research initiatives
5. Mentorship
Experienced independent researchers serve as mentors, oƯering support to newcomers.
Mentorship activities include sharing lessons learned, building new skills together, and
helping individuals navigate the independent research landscape.
6. Recognition
NIRA values contributions based on the quality and novelty of work, not formal credentials.
Recognition mechanisms include:
 Community awards for outstanding research
 Peer acknowledgment for meaningful contributions
 Publication support to amplify validated findings
 No credential requirements—recognition is based solely on good work, whether null
or novel in its findings
Community Rules
To ensure a productive and inclusive environment, the following rules guide all interactions
within NIRA:
 Evidence-based contributions only
 Rigorous methodology is required for all shared work
 Respectful disagreement is encouraged
 Tribal thinking is strictly forbidden
 Members are expected to help others improve
 Failures should be shared openly for learning purposes
 Credit is to be given generously to contributors
 Humility regarding personal limits is valued
Prohibited actions include:
 Credential gatekeeping
 Dismissing ideas without reason
 Personal attacks
 Tribal warfare
 Stealing work
 Making false claims
